{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "11", "m": "06", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "08", "M": "25", "S": "30"}}, "news": [{"title": "Gurugram: Man cons 242 home buyers through allotment fraud, held", "para": "Haryana Police's Economic Offences Wing apprehended a 33-year-old man at Delhi Airport, accused of defrauding individuals by promising flats in a Gurugram housing society. He allegedly collected crores from 242 applicants, failing to deliver homes or refunds. The accused, Anubhav Bhardwaj, was planning to flee the country when arrested.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/gurugram-man-arrested-for-conning-242-home-buyers-in-housing-society-scam/131648266?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-32594/131648266.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Punjab government to formulate policy to provide relief to residents of unauthorised colonies: CM", "para": "The Punjab government is creating a new policy to help citizens who invested in unauthorized colonies. Many families lost their savings due to dishonest developers. These developers sold plots without proper approvals, leaving residents without basic facilities like electricity and water. The government will take strict action against these developers.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/punjab-government-to-support-residents-of-unauthorized-colonies-with-new-relief-policy/131648229?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-22430/131648229.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "NCLT admits insolvency plea by 176 Raheja Developers\u2019 Revanta buyers over delayed handover", "para": "The National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) has admitted an insolvency petition against Raheja Developers' Revanta project in Gurugram. 176 homebuyers, who collectively paid over Rs 137 crore, filed the petition citing significant delays in possession beyond promised timelines. The tribunal found a prima facie case of default, noting unhonored commitments and non-compliance with regulatory directions.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/nclt-accepts-insolvency-petition-from-176-raheja-developers-homebuyers-over-handover-delays/131648201?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-111220/131648201.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}]}